# Live host communication (custom ramdisk only)

Stock Apple RestoreRamDisk from an IPSW does **not** ship a general shell agent.
It expects idevicerestore's restore/lockdown protocol.

For **host-driven upload + command execution**, build a custom overlay and stage your
own arm64 binaries from the Mac:

```bash
# Stage a cross-compiled iOS agent (or arm64 binary you supply)
./build/bin/purplepois0n --build-ramdisk /tmp/test.dmg \
  --ramdisk-overlay tests/fixtures/ramdisk_overlay \
  --ramdisk-add-macho ./build/pp-agent:/sbin/pp-agent
```

## TCP line protocol (default)

purplepois0n talks to a user-supplied listener on port **4444** by default (no sshd required):

| Command | Response |
|---------|----------|
| `PING` | `PONG` |
| `EXEC <shell>` | `OK <exit>\n` … output lines … `.` |
| `PUT /path N` + N bytes | `OK` |
| `GET /path` | `DATA N` + N bytes, or `ERR msg` |

After boot, forward the device port:

```bash
iproxy -u UDID 4444:4444
./build/bin/purplepois0n -d UDID --ramdisk-probe
./build/bin/purplepois0n -d UDID --ramdisk-exec "uname -a"
```

Use `--ramdisk-transport ssh` only if your overlay ships sshd/dropbear.

## Reference agent

Cross-compile `tests/fixtures/pp-agent/pp-agent.c` for iOS arm64 and stage with:

```bash
--ramdisk-add-macho ./pp-agent:/sbin/pp-agent
```

Launch from init via overlay `sbin/start-pp-agent`. See [tests/fixtures/pp-agent/README.md](../pp-agent/README.md).
